---
import Layout from '../layouts/Layout.astro';
---

<Layout title="About Brian Kuria | Cloud & Data Science" description="The journey from Information Technology to Cloud Architecture and Data Science.">
  <main class="max-w-3xl mx-auto px-4 py-20">
    <header class="mb-12">
      <h1 class="text-4xl md:text-5xl font-extrabold text-slate-900 dark:text-white mb-6 tracking-tight">
        The bridge between <span class="text-blue-600 dark:text-blue-400">infrastructure</span> and <span class="text-cyan-500">intelligence.</span>
      </h1>
      <p class="text-xl text-slate-600 dark:text-slate-400 leading-relaxed">
        I’m an IT professional turned Data Scientist. My goal is to build machine learning systems that are not just accurate, but production-ready and scalable.
      </p>
    </header>
    
    <div class="prose prose-slate dark:prose-invert max-w-none">
      <h2 class="text-2xl font-bold text-slate-900 dark:text-white">The Journey</h2>
      <p>
        With a degree in <strong>Information Technology</strong>, I started with a deep fascination for how systems scale. This led me to become an <strong>AWS Certified Solutions Architect & Practitioner</strong>, where I learned to build the "pipes" that run the modern web.
      </p>
      <p>
        However, I realized that the most exciting part of the infrastructure wasn't just the scaling—it was the data flowing through it. This sparked my transition into <strong>Data Science</strong> through the <strong>ALX Data Science program</strong>, where I began applying statistical rigor to real-world problems.
      </p>

      <div class="grid grid-cols-1 md:grid-cols-2 gap-6 not-prose my-12">
        <div class="p-6 rounded-2xl bg-slate-50 dark:bg-slate-900 border border-slate-200 dark:border-slate-800">
          <h3 class="font-bold text-blue-600 dark:text-blue-400 mb-2">Cloud Mastery</h3>
          <ul class="text-sm space-y-2 text-slate-600 dark:text-slate-400">
            <li>• AWS Certified Solutions Architect</li>
            <li>• Scalable Backend Architectures</li>
            <li>• FastAPI & API Deployment</li>
            <li>• PostgreSQL & Database Design</li>
          </ul>
        </div>
        <div class="p-6 rounded-2xl bg-slate-50 dark:bg-slate-900 border border-slate-200 dark:border-slate-800">
          <h3 class="font-bold text-cyan-600 dark:text-cyan-400 mb-2">Data Science</h3>
          <ul class="text-sm space-y-2 text-slate-600 dark:text-slate-400">
            <li>• Predictive Modeling (Scikit-Learn)</li>
            <li>• Deep Learning (TensorFlow/Keras)</li>
            <li>• Quantitative Finance Interests</li>
            <li>• Advanced Python (Pandas, Numpy)</li>
          </ul>
        </div>
      </div>

      <h2 class="text-2xl font-bold text-slate-900 dark:text-white">What I'm Doing Now</h2>
      <p>
        When I’m not analyzing Kenyan food price trends or building movie recommender systems, I’m deep in the <strong>LeetCode</strong> trenches—mastering stacks, queues, and linked lists to keep my algorithmic thinking sharp.
      </p>
      <p>
        I'm currently looking for roles as a <strong>Junior Python Engineer</strong> or <strong>Junior Data Scientist</strong> where I can contribute to building high-impact, data-driven applications.
      </p>

      <div class="flex flex-wrap gap-4 mt-12 not-prose">
        <a href="/contact" class="bg-blue-600 text-white px-6 py-3 rounded-xl hover:bg-blue-700 transition font-bold shadow-lg shadow-blue-500/20">
          Let's Collaborate
        </a>
        <a href="https://github.com/kobeyvines" target="_blank" class="flex items-center gap-2 bg-slate-900 dark:bg-white text-white dark:text-slate-900 px-6 py-3 rounded-xl hover:opacity-90 transition font-bold">
          See the Code
        </a>
      </div>
    </div>
  </main>
</Layout>